node.text:
These #appetizer ideas are brilliant!

1) Mortadella
INGREDIENTS
Sliced mortadella
200g cream cheese
Pistachio
Cling film

METHOD
Spread cream cheese on a slice of mortadella. Roll up and cut into medium pieces.
Sprinkle with pistachio grains.
-----------------------------------------
2) Ham
INGREDIENTS
Sliced Large bread
Rocket salad
Mayonnaise
Ham
Cling film
Poppy seeds

METHOD
Place a long slice of bread on top of cling film. Use a rolling pin to flatten. Spread mayonnaise all over the slice, add ham and rocket salad.
Roll vertically and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Spread mayonnaise on one side of the roll and add poppy seeds. Cut in pieces.
-----------------------------------------
3) Salmon
INGREDIENTS
Sliced large bread
Salmon
Salad
Cream cheese
Cling film
Chives
Poppy seeds

METHOD
Place a long slice of bread on top of cling film. Use a rolling pin to flatten.
Mix cream cheese with chives and spread over the entire slice. Add salmon and salad to the entire slice of bread.
Roll vertically and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Spread cream cheese on one side of the roll and add poppy seeds. Cut into slices.
-----------------------------------------
4) Mortadella
INGREDIENTS
Sliced mortadella
Ricotta
Pistachio
Bread
Oil
Honey

METHOD
Cut several slices of bread.
Place them in a pan until toasted.
Mix ricotta with oil and cover each bread.
Add pistachio grains, slices of mortadella, honey and more pistachios to each slice.

node.title: 4 simple and delicious appetizers to surprise everyone!

node.text:
Easy and delicious, this #zucchini roll is perfect for dinner!

INGREDIENTS
1 zucchini
4 eggs
100g (½ cup) cheese
Salt
Pepper

METHOD
Grate the zucchini. Drain the water.
Beat eggs, salt, and pepper in a mixing bowl. Add zucchini and grated cheese. Mix.
Fry the mixture in an oiled pan, slowly roll it out, and gradually add.
Cut it into pieces and serve.

node.text:
Have you ever tried to add instant coffee to your #pancakes? The result is delicious! 

INGREDIENTS
3 bananas
1 tbsp instant coffee
2 eggs
300ml milk
250g flour
10g baking powder
3 tbsp sugar
Hazelnut grains
Hazelnut cream
 
METHOD
Cut the bananas in a bowl, add instant coffee, eggs and blend very well. Add milk, flour, baking powder, sugar, and mix well.
Cook in a pan for 5 minutes on both sides.
Spread hazelnut cream on each pancake and serve with hazelnut grains.

node.text:
Ready in a few minutes, this #bread is super delicious! 
 
INGREDIENTS
900g (7 cups) flour
300ml (1 1/5 cups) warm milk
300ml (1 1/5 cups) warm water
4g (1 tsp) salt
7g dry yeast
Olive oil
Parsley

METHOD
Add flour, yeast, water, milk, and salt to the mixing bowl. Knead the dough. Leave to rest for 60 minutes.
Divide the dough into 8 parts and roll out with a rolling pin.
Bake on high heat in a pan. Coat with oil and parsley. Serve.

node.text:
These #calzones are delicious, you won't be able to stop at one! 
 
INGREDIENTS
600g (5 cups) flour
330ml (1 ¼ cups) water
10g (2 tsp) baking powder
4g (1 tsp) salt
25ml (2 tbsp) olive oil
 
Filling:
100ml (2/5 cup) tomato pasta
100g mozzarella
100g ham
100g (2/5 cup) bechamel

METHOD
In a mixing bowl add the flour, yeast, and a little water at a time, then add the salt and oil and start kneading.
Knead everything well until it forms a smooth and soft dough, then with a rolling pin roll out a sheet of about 5mm high.
With a pasta bowl, make lots of circles, stuffed with tomato and mozzarella or béchamel and cooked ham.
Then close all the panzerotti in the shape of a half-moon and seal with a fork so that the filling does not come out during cooking.
Now fry them in abundant hot oil for a couple of minutes on each side or until you see them golden. Serve.

node.text:
The two-color cake is DIVINE! Everyone will ask you the recipe!

INGREDIENTS
2 eggs
60g (1/3 cup) sugar
4g (1 tsp) vanilla sugar
60ml (¼ cup) oil
120ml (½ cup) milk
250g (2 cups) flour
10g (2 tsp) baking powder
10g (1 tbsp) cocoa powder
 
METHOD
In a mixing bowl add the eggs, sugar, vanilla, oil, and milk. Mix. Add flour and baking powder. Mix well.
Pour 80% of the mixture into a baking tin.
Mix the rest of the mixture with cocoa and make tufts on the cake.
Bake at 360°F / 180°C for 25 minutes. Garnish with powdered sugar and serve.

node.text:
This method to make delicious #fritters is genius! 
 
INGREDIENTS
300g (2 3/8 cups) flour
1/3 tsp salt
40ml (3 tbsp) oil
baking powder 10g
2 eggs
2 tbsp cocoa
hazelnut cream
powdered sugar
 

METHOD
In a bowl mix together flour with salt, oil, baking powder and eggs.
Divide the dough into 2 portions and add cocoa powder to the second. Let it rest for 20 minutes.
Divide the dough into little pieces then roll out them.
Cut it into the 4 triangles and put 7-8 triangles one on top of the other along.
Roll them and cut them into 2 pieces making flowers fasten them with toothpicks.
Fry in the hot oil until golden brown.
Serve with hazelnut cream and powdered sugar.

node.text:
If you love #zucchini, this recipe is perfect for you! 
 
INGREDIENTS
2 zucchini
4g (1 tsp) salt
4g (1 tsp) paprika

For dough:
2 eggs
200g (1 cup) yogurt
200 ml (4/5 cup) milk
10g ( 2 tsp) baking powder
4g (1 tsp) salt
Dill
125g (1 cup) flour
 
For the filling:
Cheese

METHOD
Grate the zucchini and add salt and pepper. Add eggs, yogurt, milk, salt, baking powder, dill, and flour to the mixing bowl. Mix.
Pour zucchini into an oiled pan.
Put grated cheese on them and pour over the mixture.
Cover and bake. Serve.

node.text:
This is a perfect idea to make a delicious lunch for the whole family!

INGREDIENTS
500g minced meat
1 onion
1 egg
ham slices
Cheese slices
Grilled zucchini slices
1 tsp salt
1/2 tsp black pepper
3 eggs
Flour
Breadcrumbs

METHOD
Mix together minced meat with onion, egg, salt, and black pepper.
Spread the meat on cling film, top it with cherry slices, ham slices, and grilled zucchini. Wrap in a roll and freeze for 1 hour.
Cut into slices and dip into flour eggs and breadcrumbs.
Fry in the hot oil until golden brown.

node.text:
You won't be able to stop at one!

INGREDIENTS
300g hazelnut cream
120ml (½ cup) milk
7g dry yeast
50g sugar
2 eggs
Oil
1 lime zest
260g (2 cups) flour
 
Sugar for coating
 
METHOD
Pour the hazelnut cream into small portions on the parchment paper. Leave in the freezer for 1-2 hours.
 
Dissolve the dry yeast and sugar in the milk. Add the eggs, oil, lime zest, flour and mix well.
 
Take portions of the batter with a spoon and fill them with the cold hazelnut cream.
 
Fry the mixture in boiling oil until golden.
 
Dip the pancakes in sugar and serve.

node.text:
Here're 2 amazing ideas with #tortilla!

INGREDIENTS
Tortillas
4 eggs
50g (1/2 cup) shredded cheese
1/2 tsp salt
1/3 tsp pepper
1/3 red bell pepper
1/3 yellow pepper
1/3 green pepper
80ml (1/3 cup) sour cream
 
METHOD
Make circles on tortillas by using a glass or a plate. Transfer them to a baking pan.
Mix eggs with species and shredded cheese, pour the mixture into the tortilla cups, add chopped peppers.
Bake at 180’C (350’F) for 5 minutes, sprinkle with shredded cheese and bake for 4 minutes more.
Add egg mixture to a pan and cover with tortilla, fry from both sides. Wrap it in the roll.

node.text:
If you love zucchini and chicken, these rolls are for you! 
 
INGREDIENTS
250 g ham
250g chicken breast
1 small zucchini, shredded
150 g cheese
2 egg
3 g (1/2 tsp) salt
Breadcrumbs
10ml (2 tsp) olive oil

METHOD
Cut chicken into 5-6 thin slices. Cover chicken slices with plastic wrap and beat with a meat mallet or rolling pin to tenderize the meat. Season with salt and pepper.
Shred the zucchini.
Place a slice of ham on a cutting board, arrange a piece of chicken and a slice of cheese on top.
Put some shredded zucchini on the cheese slice and wrap the roll. Continue with the remaining ingredients.
Prepare the breading station: whisk 2 eggs in a bowl, place breadcrumbs onto a separate plate.
Dip each roll in beaten eggs, then coat in breadcrumbs and place into a baking dish.
Sprinkle the rolls with olive oil and bake at 180 °C for 20 minutes.

node.text:
The scent of #mint is incredible 🌿❤️ 

Mentha, commonly known as mint leaves, are tasty herbs we often use in cooking. Traditionally, mint was used for aromatherapy, and was given the title ‘the herb of hospitality’, because of its use as a room deodorizer in olden times.

Its aroma might be pleasant to humans but it repels mosquitos, flies, fleas, and mice. You can use it to prepare infused oil and to baked preparations, beverages, face mask, and body scrub.

Did you know that you can easily grow mint at home?

node.text:
Kids will love these amazing #peanutbuttercookies!
 
INGREDIENTS
100g (1/2 cup) butter
50ml (1/4 cup) of vegetable oil
1 egg
55g (1/2 cup) of cornstarch
80g (2/3 cup) powdered sugar
5g (1 1/4 tsp) vanilla sugar
2g (1 tbsp) of cinnamon
240g (2 cups) flour
Peanut butter
 
METHOD
In a bowl add the butter, powdered sugar and mix with the spatula. Add the vegetable oil and mix again.
Add the cinnamon, vanilla sugar, cornstarch and mix again with the spatula. Add half of the flour and mix well.
Add the egg, mix with the spatula and add the rest of the flour. Mix until the batter is well combined.
With the hands create the small balls, add them to the fork, and add the little peanut butter on top. Roll them on the fork to create a round shape.
Transfer the cookies to the baking tray and bake at 356°F/180°C for 15 minutes.

node.text:
These #appetizer ideas are brilliant!

1) Mortadella
INGREDIENTS
Sliced mortadella
200g cream cheese
Pistachio
Cling film

METHOD
Spread cream cheese on a slice of mortadella. Roll up and cut into medium pieces.
Sprinkle with pistachio grains.
-----------------------------------------
2) Ham
INGREDIENTS
Sliced Large bread
Rocket salad
Mayonnaise
Ham
Cling film
Poppy seeds

METHOD
Place a long slice of bread on top of cling film. Use a rolling pin to flatten. Spread mayonnaise all over the slice, add ham and rocket salad.
Roll vertically and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Spread mayonnaise on one side of the roll and add poppy seeds. Cut in pieces.
-----------------------------------------
3) Salmon
INGREDIENTS
Sliced large bread
Salmon
Salad
Cream cheese
Cling film
Chives
Poppy seeds

METHOD
Place a long slice of bread on top of cling film. Use a rolling pin to flatten.
Mix cream cheese with chives and spread over the entire slice. Add salmon and salad to the entire slice of bread.
Roll vertically and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Spread cream cheese on one side of the roll and add poppy seeds. Cut into slices.
-----------------------------------------
4) Mortadella
INGREDIENTS
Sliced mortadella
Ricotta
Pistachio
Bread
Oil
Honey

METHOD
Cut several slices of bread.
Place them in a pan until toasted.
Mix ricotta with oil and cover each bread.
Add pistachio grains, slices of mortadella, honey and more pistachios to each slice.

node.text:
Easy and delicious, this #zucchini roll is perfect for dinner!

INGREDIENTS
1 zucchini
4 eggs
100g (½ cup) cheese
Salt
Pepper

METHOD
Grate the zucchini. Drain the water.
Beat eggs, salt, and pepper in a mixing bowl. Add zucchini and grated cheese. Mix.
Fry the mixture in an oiled pan, slowly roll it out, and gradually add.
Cut it into pieces and serve.

node.text:
#Cherrycake: fluffy and soft, everyone will love it!

INGREDIENTS
550g (4 cups) pitted cherries
3 eggs
200g (1.6 cup) flour 00
100g + 50 g of sugar
50g (0.2 cup) butter in curls
15ml (3 tsp) milk
5g (1 tsp) Baking powder
15g (1 tbsp) Vanilla sugar
 
METHOD
In a large bowl, pour the eggs and 100 g of sugar, whisk the mixture with a mixer. Add milk, vanilla sugar, then flour and baking powder and whisk everything into a fine, smooth mixture.
Add the cherries to the mixture and combine them by mixing with a spatula.
Preheat the oven to 180°C, line a 24 cm mold with baking paper.
Pour the mixture into a previously prepared mold, flatten and sprinkle the surface with 50g of sugar and 50g of butter in curls. Bake at 180°C for about 40-45 minutes.

node.text:
Have you ever tried to add instant coffee to your #pancakes? The result is delicious! 

INGREDIENTS
3 bananas
1 tbsp instant coffee
2 eggs
300ml milk
250g flour
10g baking powder
3 tbsp sugar
Hazelnut grains
Hazelnut cream
 
METHOD
Cut the bananas in a bowl, add instant coffee, eggs and blend very well. Add milk, flour, baking powder, sugar, and mix well.
Cook in a pan for 5 minutes on both sides.
Spread hazelnut cream on each pancake and serve with hazelnut grains.

Ready in a few minutes, this #bread is super delicious! 
 
INGREDIENTS
900g (7 cups) flour
300ml (1 1/5 cups) warm milk
300ml (1 1/5 cups) warm water
4g (1 tsp) salt
7g dry yeast
Olive oil
Parsley

METHOD
Add flour, yeast, water, milk, and salt to the mixing bowl. Knead the dough. Leave to rest for 60 minutes.
Divide the dough into 8 parts and roll out with a rolling pin.
Bake on high heat in a pan. Coat with oil and parsley. Serve.
